# client/.env.production — environment variables baked into the React build for production.
#
# This file is safe to commit — it contains no secrets, only the API base URL.
# CRA inlines REACT_APP_* variables at build time; they are not read at runtime.
#
# REACT_APP_SERVER_URL is the base URL prepended to every API call in client.js:
#   const BASE_URL = process.env.REACT_APP_SERVER_URL || 'http://localhost:3001';
#
# Why /api (not empty):
#   On Vercel, the React frontend and Express backend share the same domain.
#   vercel.json routes /api/* to the Express serverless function and everything
#   else to the React SPA.  Setting BASE_URL to /api means the client makes
#   requests like GET /api/auth/me, which Vercel correctly forwards to Express.
#   Express then strips the /api prefix via path-strip middleware in index.js
#   so the route handlers continue to use their original paths.
#
#   An empty value would fall back to 'http://localhost:3001' (the || default in
#   client.js), which does not work in production.
REACT_APP_SERVER_URL=/api

